|CKBSecond Spur|000

|CK0Second Spur is passive off-hand firmware unlocked at Street Samurai Guild
Level 13. It requires the left-hand Second Spur implant and has no activation
command, SP cost, Edge cost, or Heat cost.|000

|CKBExpanded Edge capacity|000
|CK0While the implant is online, it raises maximum Edge above the normal cap.
Better grades can provide additional headroom when the spur is well maintained.
The monitor, samstatus, dashboard, and samwho all report the resulting live
maximum rather than assuming a fixed value.|000

|CKBOff-hand cutting line|000
|CK0Second Spur gives Chrome Tempest an additional cutting line. Stronger,
well-maintained hardware can contribute more to the sequence. The spur must be
installed and online when Tempest begins; installing it after the sequence
starts does not alter that activation.|000

|CK0The second line also joins an armed Monowire Edge breach. It does not arm
the breach itself: deploy Monowire, use monowire edge, and let the next
confirmed hit trigger both lines.|000

|CKBHardware benefits|000
|CK0The implant adds +4/+6/+8/+10 damage stat and +2/+3/+4/+5 critical stat
from prototype through ghost grade. Every confirmed weapon hit can invoke an
independent off-hand cut. Better grades increase its chance from 11% to 20%
and reduce its cooldown from 12 seconds to 6 seconds.|000

|CK0The cut deals armour-piercing slash damage that scales with your level,
Street Samurai Guild Level, hardware grade, Cortex power, and firmware
effectiveness. A damaging cut generates 1 Edge. If another valid enemy is
already attacking you, the filament cleaves that enemy for half damage. This
proc has no SP, Edge, or Heat cost.|000

|CK0Low Second Spur or Cortex integrity and high Second Spur fragmentation
weaken the cut, Edge-cap bonus, and Chrome Tempest contribution without taking
the spur completely offline. Use dashboard and implants to inspect it.|000
